05:11.968 --> 05:15.570
Hey, how about
that Asian fusion place?

05:15.572 --> 05:18.173
Fusion and Asians?

05:18.175 --> 05:21.443
I'm trying not to
think about science.

05:21.445 --> 05:23.545
What the hell?

05:25.114 --> 05:26.047
What...?

05:26.049 --> 05:27.382
She's not working late!

05:28.317 --> 05:30.685
And Amy doesn't
look sick.

05:30.687 --> 05:32.153
Why would they
lie to us?

05:32.155 --> 05:33.455
That's a good question.

05:33.457 --> 05:34.556
(knocking)

05:34.558 --> 05:35.423
Amy and Bernadette.

05:35.425 --> 05:36.324
(knocking)

05:36.326 --> 05:37.726
Amy and Bernadette.
(knocking)

05:37.728 --> 05:39.060
Amy and Bernadette.

05:39.062 --> 05:41.696
Why did you lie to us?!

05:44.333 --> 05:47.135
Hey. Listen to this:

05:47.137 --> 05:49.738
"Murder... cannibalism

05:49.740 --> 05:51.273
"and satanic rituals

05:51.275 --> 05:52.407
"are just a few

05:52.409 --> 05:55.076
of the thousand plus
horrors that await."

05:55.078 --> 05:57.145
I just helped my mom
out of the tub,

05:57.147 --> 05:59.848
so, I'm one slippery horror
ahead of you.

05:59.850 --> 06:01.049
You're a good son.

06:01.051 --> 06:03.285
I don't know how you do it.

06:03.287 --> 06:05.020
Beach blankets,
my friend.

06:05.022 --> 06:06.721
It's all about
beach blankets.

06:06.723 --> 06:10.158
All right,
let's get this over with.

06:10.160 --> 06:13.595
Ew, it's got
someone's hair on it!

06:13.597 --> 06:15.330
Oh, yeah, you're gonna
do great with this movie.

06:15.332 --> 06:16.731
(blows)

06:19.969 --> 06:22.671
You're not working late.
Why did you lie to me?

06:22.673 --> 06:24.939
And Amy, you told me
you were sick,

06:24.941 --> 06:27.842
but you look just as pale
and tired as always.

06:29.412 --> 06:31.179
I'm sorry.
I just needed a break

06:31.181 --> 06:34.182
from hearing you obsess about
what to do after string theory.

06:34.184 --> 06:36.351
And we kind of just
wanted one night

06:36.353 --> 06:38.720
where we didn't have to hear
about how miserable you are

06:38.722 --> 06:40.455
making this movie.

06:40.457 --> 06:42.557
But none of that means
we don't love you.

06:42.559 --> 06:45.193
I haven't been complaining
that much about the movie.

06:45.195 --> 06:47.762
Have I?

06:48.664 --> 06:50.031
I also love you.

06:53.436 --> 06:54.736
You know what?

06:54.738 --> 06:56.538
Maybe I need a break from
all of you.

06:56.540 --> 06:58.773
Come on, Sheldon.

06:58.775 --> 06:59.614
Where are we going?

06:59.639 --> 07:01.577
We're gonna have Anything Can
Happen Thursday, you're gonna

07:01.578 --> 07:03.545
tell me all about your science
stuff and I'm gonna complain

07:03.547 --> 07:05.280
about my movie, and we're gonna
support each other because

07:05.282 --> 07:06.448
that's what friends do.

07:06.450 --> 07:07.716
Okay.

07:07.718 --> 07:09.751
'Cause if I
had to pick now,

07:09.753 --> 07:10.681
I'd probably go with
dark matter because...

07:10.706 --> 07:12.706
PENNY: Shut up.

