this hodgepodge of ethnicity.

07:54.759 --> 07:56.994
Think I've been complaining
too much about the movie?

07:56.996 --> 07:58.796
Not at all.

07:58.798 --> 08:00.230
Thank you.

08:00.232 --> 08:02.399
But to be fair, when you talk,
most of what you say

08:02.401 --> 08:06.170
sounds like, "Wah,
wah, wah, clothes".

08:09.741 --> 08:12.042
Hey, I don't understand
why you're not upset with Amy.

08:12.044 --> 08:14.611
I am. So much so that
I'm gonna bring her here

08:14.613 --> 08:16.847
for dinner on our
next date night.

08:19.784 --> 08:21.985
(heavy metal soundtrack
plays on movie)

08:27.158 --> 08:29.159
Okay.

08:29.161 --> 08:31.862
So, in the last 20 minutes,

08:31.864 --> 08:34.664
we've seen a crazy woman
kissing a fetus in a jar.

08:36.067 --> 08:39.602
We've seen a guy
cut in half and sewn to a fish.

08:40.972 --> 08:43.807
And the brutal dismemberment
of a rotisserie chicken

08:43.808 --> 08:46.009
by my mother.

08:47.245 --> 08:51.582
On the bright side, she didn't
even notice the pill.

08:53.785 --> 08:56.453
Why does Emily like this stuff?

08:56.455 --> 08:58.655
Do you think there's something
psychologically wrong with her?

08:58.657 --> 09:01.125
What difference does it make?
What do you mean?

09:01.127 --> 09:02.759
Oh, come on-- she could
have a freezer full of

09:02.761 --> 09:05.596
ex-boyfriend's body parts and
you'd still go out with her.

09:06.764 --> 09:08.398
I do like that
the ex-boyfriend's

09:08.400 --> 09:09.833
out of the picture.

09:13.938 --> 09:16.039
I feel so bad about
lying to Sheldon.

09:16.041 --> 09:17.808
How am I gonna
make it up to him?

09:17.810 --> 09:19.476
I'd tell you
what I do with Howard,

09:19.478 --> 09:21.778
but I don't think dressing up
like a Catholic schoolgirl

09:21.780 --> 09:24.848
is gonna work with Sheldon.

09:27.385 --> 09:29.486
He'd probably give you homework.

09:33.725 --> 09:35.926
Did you lie to Howard
about tonight?

09:35.928 --> 09:36.960
Of course.

09:36.962 --> 09:38.595
And you don't feel
guilty about it?

09:38.597 --> 09:39.863
Between Penny's gorilla movie

09:39.865 --> 09:43.367
and Howard's gorilla mother,
I had no choice.

09:44.435 --> 09:45.869
Thankfully Penny and I have

09:45.871 --> 09:47.304
a relationship based on honesty.

09:47.306 --> 09:48.805
(snorts)

09:48.807 --> 09:50.440
What?

09:50.442 --> 09:51.775
I don't lie to her.

09:51.777 --> 09:54.378
Oh, we know
<i>you</i> don't lie to <i>her.</i>

10:00.585 --> 10:02.085
Thank you.

10:02.087 --> 10:03.320
Hey, maybe the answer

10:03.322 --> 10:05.889
to your career question is
in one of these.

10:05.891 --> 10:08.659
Penny,
there's only one cookie

10:08.661 --> 10:11.094
with something in the middle
that solves life's problems,

10:11.096 --> 10:13.163
and that's an Oreo.

10:14.365 --> 10:18.335
Or a Nutter Butter,
if you're in a pinch.

10:18.337 --> 10:21.138
Come on, open it.
I bet it says something great.

10:21.140 --> 10:22.940
This is Asian fusion.

10:22.942 --> 10:27.144
For all you know, there's
a tiny Chihuahua in here.

10:27.146 --> 10:29.112
Fine, I'll go.

10:29.114 --> 10:31.014
Hmm.

10:31.016 --> 10:33.917
"People turn to you
for guidance and wisdom."

10:33.919 --> 10:35.219
Yeah, that's a good one.

10:35.221 --> 10:37.321
No, it's not.

10:37.323 --> 10:38.755
How is that not good?

10:38.757 --> 10:40.991
"Turn to you for wisdom"?

10:40.993 --> 10:43.694
Clearly,
that cookie is mocking you.

10:44.696 --> 10:46.296
You'd never hear
that kind of sass

10:46.298 --> 10:48.298
from a Nutter Butter.

10:48.300 --> 10:50.701
Uh, since you're paying for
dinner, I'll let that slide.

10:50.703 --> 10:52.135
Open yours.

10:53.771 --> 10:55.772
Have you ever paid for a meal?

10:55.774 --> 10:57.341
Not with money. Read.

