mumbo jumbo.

13:22.454 --> 13:24.888
Well, Penny can be
pretty persuasive.

13:24.890 --> 13:27.924
She's gotten me to do a lot of
things I wouldn't normally do.

13:27.926 --> 13:29.860
Because she has
sex with you.

13:29.862 --> 13:32.896
Yeah, she does.

13:32.898 --> 13:35.265
Can I confess something?

13:35.267 --> 13:37.167
Once in a while,
I get a little jealous

13:37.169 --> 13:38.602
of how close Penny
and Sheldon are.

13:38.604 --> 13:39.668
Really?

13:39.693 --> 13:41.272
I mean, not in
a romantic way.

13:41.273 --> 13:44.741
It's just, she really has some
sort of connection with him.

13:44.743 --> 13:47.477
Well... Well, they've known
each other a long time,

13:47.479 --> 13:49.846
and Penny grew up around horses,

13:49.848 --> 13:53.650
so she knows how to approach him
without making him skittish.

13:53.652 --> 13:55.886
Don't get me wrong.
I'm glad they're friends.

13:55.888 --> 13:58.355
I just wish he'd be that
comfortable around me already.

13:58.357 --> 14:02.726
Well, it took him a long time to
get comfortable around me, too.

14:02.728 --> 14:05.028
Really? What did you do?

14:05.030 --> 14:08.498
Something terrible in a former life?
I don't know.

14:08.500 --> 14:11.034
I gotta go.

14:11.036 --> 14:12.636
Penny ratted me out.

14:12.638 --> 14:14.404
FYI, she's getting you
a watch for your birthday

14:14.406 --> 14:16.206
with money she took
out of your wallet.

14:22.280 --> 14:25.949
I don't mean to be
rude or discourteous,

14:25.951 --> 14:27.784
but before we begin,
I'd just like to say

14:27.786 --> 14:30.353
there is absolutely
no scientific evidence

14:30.355 --> 14:32.689
to support clairvoyance
of any kind.

14:32.691 --> 14:34.591
Which means--

14:34.593 --> 14:38.862
and again, no insult intended--
but you're a fraud...

14:39.697 --> 14:41.832
...your profession
is a swindle,

14:41.834 --> 14:43.366
and, uh, your livelihood
is dependent

14:43.368 --> 14:46.236
on the gullibility
of stupid people.

14:47.572 --> 14:50.640
Again, no offense.

14:50.642 --> 14:52.409
All right, Sheldon,
just ask your question.

14:52.411 --> 14:55.612
(clears his throat)

14:55.614 --> 14:58.248
Okay, I just did.
What was it?

14:59.183 --> 15:00.517
Oh, for God's sake.

15:00.519 --> 15:01.818
Look, he's a physicist
who's trying to figure out

15:01.820 --> 15:03.119
what his next field
of study should be.

15:03.121 --> 15:04.321
For your information,

15:04.323 --> 15:07.290
I was asking her
about the next <i>Star Trek</i> movie.

15:07.292 --> 15:11.094
Okay, I can answer that one:
I'll be bored.

15:11.096 --> 15:13.363
All right, why don't we begin?

15:13.365 --> 15:15.632
(sighs)

15:15.634 --> 15:17.801
(exhales deeply)

15:21.138 --> 15:23.073
Your spirit guides
are telling me

15:23.075 --> 15:25.175
that there's a woman
in your life

15:25.177 --> 15:27.177
you're having problems with.

15:27.179 --> 15:29.346
That's an easy guess.

15:29.348 --> 15:31.047
I'm clearly an annoying person

15:31.049 --> 15:33.550
and have problems
with both genders.

15:33.552 --> 15:36.753
Yes, you clearly are.

15:38.055 --> 15:39.356
But I'm seeing

15:39.358 --> 15:40.957
a specific woman

15:40.959 --> 15:43.593
that you're in a romantic
relationship with.

15:43.595 --> 15:45.929
Oh, oh, here we go.

15:46.998 --> 15:48.064
Does she have dark hair?

15:48.066 --> 15:52.068
Yes! Yes! Your spirit guides
are on fire!

15:52.070 --> 15:54.271
The majority
of people have dark hair.

15:54.273 --> 15:56.773
Even you, at one time.

15:57.942 --> 15:59.809
Does she work
in a similar field to you?

15:59.811 --> 16:01.411
Ha! The opposite.

16:01.413 --> 16:04.581
She's a neurobiologist, and
I'm a theoretical physicist.

16:04.583 --> 16:06.816
My spirit guides
can go suck an egg.

16:08.052 --> 16:09.352
They're telling me

16:09.354 --> 16:11.788
that you have difficulty
being close with her.

16:11.790 --> 16:14.324
Oh, he does. He <i>so</i> does.
What should he do?

16:14.326 --> 16:16.526
(exhales)

16:18.362 --> 16:20.864
He should give himself
to this relationship.

16:20.866 --> 16:22.933
Once he does, all his

16:22.935 --> 16:25.168
other pursuits will come
into focus.

16:25.170 --> 16:26.469
Sheldon, do you hear that?

16:26.471 --> 16:28.805
I mean, Amy is the key
to your happiness.

16:28.807 --> 16:30.006
Exactly.

16:30.008 --> 16:31.841
Personally and professionally.

16:31.843 --> 16:36.046
Everything will fall into place
once you commit to her.

16:41.185 --> 16:43.286
You know what this is?

16:43.288 --> 16:46.289
Yeah, and I reserve this word
for those rare instances

16:46.291 --> 16:47.991
when it's truly deserved.

16:47.993 --> 16:50.293
This is malarkey!

16:54.865 --> 16:56.533
Wow, you really struck a nerve.

16:56.535 --> 16:59.469
I've never heard him use
the "M" word before.

17:08.252 --> 17:09.753
Here we go:

17:09.756 --> 17:11.756
<i>House of a 1,000 Corpses.</i>

17:11.758 --> 17:13.558
Now, just so you know,

17:13.560 --> 17:16.294
I was a nanny for three years,
so if you get scared,

17:16.296 --> 17:18.529
I can totally change
your diaper.

17:18.531 --> 17:22.098
Actually, I have to
tell you something.

17:22.101 --> 17:25.368
These kind of movies
really aren't my thing,

17:25.371 --> 17:27.305
so, last night,
I watched it

17:27.327 --> 17:28.766
just to see what I was
getting myself into.

17:28.791 --> 17:30.375
Okay.

17:30.376 --> 17:32.476
And I have to be honest--
I thought it was

17:32.478 --> 17:35.379
disturbing and weird,
and it made me wonder

17:35.381 --> 17:37.582
what it says about
someone who enjoys it.

17:37.584 --> 17:39.750
I wonder that, too.

17:39.752 --> 17:41.752
Then, why do you
watch these things?

17:41.754 --> 17:44.488
Can I tell you something
without you judging me?

17:44.490 --> 17:46.457
Sure.

17:46.459 --> 17:48.459
They kind of turn me on.

17:48.461 --> 17:51.095
And play.

17:51.097 --> 17:53.331
(eerie sound effects,
heavy metal soundtrack playing)

17:56.435 --> 17:58.102
MAN (in distorted voice):
Attention...

17:59.237 --> 18:01.439
(knocking)

18:03.208 --> 18:05.176
Hello.

18:05.178 --> 18:06.844
I didn't expect you
this evening.

18:06.846 --> 18:08.813
Well, I was just feeling so bad

18:08.815 --> 18:10.514
about lying to you
the other night,

18:10.516 --> 18:13.217
I wanted to make it up to you.

18:13.219 --> 18:15.553
And how do you propose
to do that?

18:26.982 --> 18:29.318
Unless you have <i>Gravity</i>
on Blu-ray under that skirt,

18:29.319 --> 18:30.851
I don't know
where you're going with this.

